{"key":"post-12115172","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12115172</id>\n<content>The purpose of the black plastic bag is to adhere to the substrate and shrink as the substrate shrinks, thus preventing side pinning.&amp;nbsp; Many growers mistake this for 'blocking the light', but actually, it's the elimination of the gap around the edge of the tray that prevents side pinning.&amp;nbsp; Light any where on a mycelium network will stimulate pinning anywhere else on the substrate where conditions are right.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12115198</next>\n<prev>12115146</prev>\n<first>12051562</first>\n<last>12277377</last>\n<when>1267405127</when>\n<utime>03/01/10 02:58 AM</utime>\n</post>"}